						<summary>

						<p>On the seventh pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 38: 944-45 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of a fly-whisk coated with gold and silver, by Mūttakiḻāṉaḍigaḷ, the daughter of Kāḍupaṭṭigaḷ. </p>						

